The paper deals with algorithms for sparsifying graphs and hypergraphs, which are fundamental problems in computer science. The paper also discusses applications in semidefinite programming and unique games, which are important topics in theoretical computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
